# Loomky API — Project Structure & AI Rules

## Stack
Node.js + TypeScript, Express, Inversify DI, MongoDB/Mongoose, Zod validation, JWT auth, bcrypt

## demoTest Layout
```
src/
├── models/base.model.ts              # BaseSchema, IBaseModel (shared)
├── constants/database.constants.ts   # modelNames for collections
├── modules/<feature>/
│   ├── models/                       # Mongoose model (uses BaseSchema + modelNames)
│   ├── validations/                  # Zod schemas (CreateXSchema, UpdateXSchema)
│   ├── dtos/                         # z.infer types from validations only
│   ├── repositories/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── controllers/
│   └── routes/
├── utils/validation.utils.ts         # isValidMongoId
└── repositories/base.repository.ts
```

## Model Pattern (match loomky-api)
- Interface extends `IBaseModel` with `_id: Types.ObjectId`
- Schema fields + `userSchema.add(BaseSchema)`
- Export via `model(modelNames.X.modelName, schema, modelNames.X.collectionName)`
- Indexes with `partialFilterExpression: { deletedAt: null }`
- Pre-save hooks with `HydratedDocument` + `MongooseError`

## DTO Pattern (match loomky-api)
- Schemas defined in `validations/*.validation.ts`
- DTOs in `dtos/*.dto.ts` as `z.infer<typeof XSchema.body>` only
- No manual DTO interfaces; no helpers folder in modules

## Module Rules
- No top-level controllers/ or models/ for features (shared base.model only)
- No queues/workers/producers
- Soft delete via `deletedAt` field

## AI Checklist
1. Validation schema first → DTO via z.infer
2. Model uses BaseSchema + modelNames
3. DI + routes registered
4. Minimal diff
